WEBVTT

00:03.407 --> 00:05.967
Quit playing with the knobs.

00:06.310 --> 00:10.337
I'm not playing, I just can't stand to look
at a picture that's not properly adjusted.

00:11.381 --> 00:13.110
It's too green.

00:13.984 --> 00:15.542
It's too green.

00:18.755 --> 00:20.450
Perfect.

00:20.624 --> 00:22.251
I just cannot believe it!

00:22.426 --> 00:25.953
The judge is gonna be on a TV talk show.
Isn't this exciting?

00:26.129 --> 00:29.759
Yeah, lash me to the sofa.

00:30.335 --> 00:31.768
What is that?

00:31.936 --> 00:36.373
That is Jennifer Black, one of the biggest
rock stars around.

00:36.541 --> 00:40.671
- You don't say. What's she done?
- Her big hit was "Suicide Hayride."

00:41.713 --> 00:45.581
<i>Yes, based on a theme from
Beethoven's Appassionata, I believe.</i>

00:45.750 --> 00:47.684
I didn't know that.

00:47.952 --> 00:51.854
Yes, it's a fact. Many of our most modern,
popular songs are based on the classics.

00:52.023 --> 00:53.388
- Dan.
- "Wichita Lineman."

00:53.558 --> 00:55.526
<i>Wagner's Die Götterdämmerung.</i>

00:56.361 --> 00:57.589
Come in.

00:58.997 --> 01:01.522
I'm looking for Judge Harold T. Stone.

01:01.699 --> 01:04.532
Oh, sorry, you missed him.
He left about a half an hour ago.

01:04.702 --> 01:08.365
He had to hurry across town. He's gonna
be on this TV program in a few minutes.

01:08.540 --> 01:10.007
Who gives a flying...

01:13.244 --> 01:14.643
Any of us help you?

01:14.812 --> 01:18.509
No. His court clerk is sick,
and I'm filling in for her tomorrow.

01:18.684 --> 01:21.482
Well, welcome. I'm Liz Williams.

01:21.654 --> 01:24.919
- This is Dan Fielding.
- Forget it. I'm just a temporary.

01:25.090 --> 01:27.183
If I know your names,
we might become friends.

01:27.359 --> 01:29.827
If we become friends,
I'll grieve for you if you die.

01:29.995 --> 01:33.692
For a lousy couple of days?
It's not worth the pain.

01:33.866 --> 01:35.663
See you tomorrow.

01:38.971 --> 01:41.701
- That's a strange lady.
- Yeah.

01:42.174 --> 01:47.043
- Nice outfit, though.
- Look. I think it's time for Harry.

01:49.048 --> 01:50.948
<i>The singer, Jennifer Black.</i>

01:51.116 --> 01:55.314
<i>The album, I Bite the Songs.</i>

01:55.921 --> 01:58.048
Jennifer, it's been wonderful
having you here.

01:58.223 --> 01:59.588
And if you can stick around...

01:59.758 --> 02:01.953
...l'd love you to meet my next guest.
- Sure.

02:02.127 --> 02:03.992
He is one of New York's newest judges...

02:04.163 --> 02:06.791
...and one of the youngest men ever
to hold such a post.

02:06.966 --> 02:08.627
Let's make him feel right at home.

02:08.801 --> 02:11.464
The honorable, Harold T. Stone.

02:14.507 --> 02:17.476
Welcome. Welcome.

02:18.378 --> 02:20.346
- Thanks.
- So, what do we call you?

02:20.513 --> 02:22.037
- Your Honor?
- Harry's fine.

02:22.215 --> 02:25.343
- Harry, please say hello to Jennifer Black.
- Hi.

02:25.518 --> 02:29.079
Hey, nifty outfit. Boy, that must make
a lot of noise in the dryer, huh?

02:31.825 --> 02:35.955
- So, Harry, being one of New York's...
- You know, this set looks bigger on TV.

02:36.129 --> 02:39.963
It's that little lens out there.
Optical illusion, that sort of thing. Anyway...

02:40.133 --> 02:43.591
You know, this is the first time
I ever wore makeup.

02:43.770 --> 02:46.534
Looks like I'm losing control around here.

02:46.706 --> 02:51.109
Let's find out if I gain control back
after this short commercial break.

02:51.745 --> 02:54.111
Charlie, who the hell booked this show?

02:54.614 --> 02:57.014
- You're funny.
- Well, everybody says so.

02:57.183 --> 02:58.514
Are you a fan of mine?

03:00.421 --> 03:03.151
Well, I guess you'd say my tastes
are more traditional.

03:03.324 --> 03:04.951
Mel Tormé is my favorite.

03:05.126 --> 03:07.651
- Me too.
- No kidding.

03:07.828 --> 03:10.194
- I love him.
- This is the same Jennifer Black...

03:10.364 --> 03:13.197
...who wrote "Society of Scum"?

03:13.501 --> 03:17.301
I don't know, but why don't we find out
over coffee, after the show?

03:17.905 --> 03:20.100
Coffee with Jennifer Black, superstar?

03:20.541 --> 03:22.236
No. With me.

03:23.544 --> 03:25.409
- Sure.
- Tell him I don't want any more...

03:25.579 --> 03:29.572
...child actors on the show. Last night, that
little creep upstaged me the moment she...

03:29.750 --> 03:32.548
Thank you. Thank you very much.

03:32.720 --> 03:35.382
We're back talking right now
with singer Jennifer Black...

03:35.556 --> 03:37.888
...and New York judge, Harold T. Stone...

03:39.326 --> 03:41.590
...is doing the same.

